meta {
  name: POST lock/unlock action (SPIN required)
  type: http
  seq: 15
}

post {
  url: {{mal_url}}/api/bs/rlu/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/lock
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{vw_access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/vnd.vwg.mbb.RemoteLockUnlock_v1_0_0+xml
  x-securityToken: PASTE_x-securityToken_FROM_SPIN_FLOW_HERE
  X-App-Name: Volkswagen
  X-App-Version: 3.63.2
  User-Agent: Volkswagen/3.63.2-android/14
}

docs {
  STUFE 5b — Lock/Unlock (REQUIRES SPIN)

  URL (grounded — DEX + upstream): lock/unlock is the PATH TAIL, no
  brand/country segment, EMPTY body:
    POST {mal_url}/api/bs/rlu/v1/vehicles/{vin}/lock
    POST {mal_url}/api/bs/rlu/v1/vehicles/{vin}/unlock
  The old /{brand}/{country}/.../actions form with an <rluAction> XML body
  is the deprecated pre-2019 variant — both current upstream impls
  (audi_connect_ha, volkswagencarnet) and the We Connect / Skoda DEX use
  the path-tail form with NO body.

  HEADERS — KRITISCH:
    x-securityToken: <token aus 14_GET_spin_challenge>
    Header-Name ist "x-securityToken" (DEX + beide upstream-Impls) —
    NICHT "X-mbbSecToken". HTTP-Header sind case-insensitiv, aber matche
    die App. X-MbbUserId (= sub-Claim des Tokens) zusätzlich senden;
    manche Endpoints 403en ohne ihn.

    Content-Type MUSS application/vnd.vwg.mbb.RemoteLockUnlock_v1_0_0+xml
    sein — application/xml wird mit 415 abgelehnt. Body bleibt LEER.

  ERWARTETE ANTWORT (200/202):
    {
      "rluActionResponse": {
        "requestId": "abc-456-def",
        "vin": "WVWZZZAUZFW805377",
        "actionState": "queued"
      }
    }

  POLLING:
    GET {mal_url}/api/bs/rlu/v1/vehicles/{vin}/requests/{requestId}/status
    bis status ∈ {request_successful, request_fail}

  GOLF 7 GTE QUIRK:
    Lock-Befehl funktioniert nur wenn ALLE Türen geschlossen + Schlüssel
    NICHT im Auto. Sonst kommt status=request_fail mit reasonCode=
    "doors-open" oder "key-detected".

  HA ENTITIES (Phase 3 v1.28):
    lock.car_lock
      lock()   → POST <action>lock</action>
      unlock() → POST <action>unlock</action>
      state    → aus VSR field 0x0301040001 (FL door lock)

  REFERENZ:
    upstream:audi_services.py:lock + unlock
}
